    {
      "mode": "character",
      "text": "You pause in your research and take a moment to survey your surroundings.\n\nThe Whispering Archives lives up to its name\u2014a gentle hush pervades the space, broken only by the soft clink of brass fixtures and the distant whisper of turning pages. Morning light streams through the magnificent stained glass windows, casting fracturedRainbow colors across the circular chamber. Towering shelves spiral outward from the central reading desk like the ribs of some vast wooden beast, each row labeled in elegant silver script.\n\nTo your left, the public stacks stretch endless\u2014histories, treatises, mundane catalogs. You've already mined those thoroughly.\n\nTo your right, past the reading desk where Thalindor nervously shuffles papers, a dark archway leads to the restricted section. A velvet rope\u2014more symbolic than functional\u2014blocks the entrance. Two armored guards stand at attention there, though their eyes wander to the exits more than to any patrons.\n\nThalindor himself watches you with barely concealed anxiety. The elf's long fingers twitch toward a drawer in his desk\u2014locked, by the look of it\u2014and he catches himself, smoothing his expression into forced neutrality. Clearly, your discovery has not gone unnoticed.",
